This is the session which is going to make cs50 the cs50 .
We are going to study about Pointers , Segmentation Faults , Dynamic Memory Allocation, Stack , Heap , Buffer Overflow , File I/O Images .
What are Pointers ?
Pointers are reference to the variables or the address of the variables. 
*n 
&n

What are Segmentation Faults ?
Segmentation Faults are the faults which occurs when we try to touch the memory which is not allocated for the particular variables .

What is Dynamic Memory Allocation ?
Dynamic Memory Allocation is the allocation of memory when there is any requirement. 

What is Stack ?
Stack is the allocation of the system memory upon the creation of the variable or functions ,it helps in the running of the program smoothly . 

What is heap memory ?
Heap memory stores the global variables used by the program . 

What is buffer overflow ?
Buffer Overflow is the overflow of the stack and the heap memory . 


