All we see in our machine is pixels. When we talk about the image which we are seeing in our computer , it is actually the pixels .
So , in terms of the machine when we write programming , we write code in binary and decimal representation . 
But when we talk about the colours it is represented in the Hexa Decimal format .

0123456789ABCDEF

Till this time , we were using the string keyword in the c programming but what is it behind the scenes. 
string is just char* 
when we call the char* s = (It gives us the memory to story the string)

char *s = Kishan;
%s - s (This will give us the value of the complete string)
printf("The address is %p \n", s);
    printf("The address is %p \n", &s[0]);
    printf("The value prsent in the s is %c \n",s[4]);
    printf("The value prsent in the s is %s \n",s);
    printf("The value prsent in the s is %c \n",*s);
    printf("The value prsent in the s is %c \n",*(s+1));

    printf("The value prsent in the s is %c \n",s[1]);


When we compare the strings , we basically compare the addresses instead of the values . 
so we need to use strcmp
when we copy the strings , we basically copy the address , a slight change in one is going to result a change with the same string  .
 

